Zimbabwe may have taken another step towards relaunching its dollar, but on the streets of the capital Harare people are nervous. Locals say that they do not know what the future holds. On Monday, the interim currency - the RTGS Dollar - became the country's sole legal tender, ending a decade-long use of multiple currencies including the USD and the ZAR. Zimbabwe outages plunge businesses into darkness Zimbabwean President Emmerson Mnangagwa promised a ''brighter tomorrow'' when he was sworn in, vowing to revive the country's economy after Robert Mugabe's 37-year rule. But this week Zimbabwe is firmly in the dark, as it endures the worst power cuts in three years.